# Frontend interaction safety

## Root cause (do not repeat)

Links felt broken for two reasons:

1. **Overlapping sections blocked clicks** — `LandingFeatures` uses negative margin (`-mt-14`) and sits at `z-20` above the hero (`z-10`). Its opaque `bg-landing-light` covered hero CTAs in the overlap band and intercepted pointer events.
2. **No navigation feedback** — routes like `/curriculum` eagerly import the full question bank and can take 30–60s to compile in dev. Without a loading indicator, clicks look dead.

## Rules

### Overlapping layout layers

- Decorative or overlapping sections MUST use `pointer-events-none` on the wrapper.
- Interactive children MUST re-enable with `pointer-events-auto`.
- Hero CTAs and nav links MUST sit above overlapping sections (`z-30+` for interactive hero content vs `z-20` for overlapping panels).

```tsx
// ✅ Overlap passes clicks through to content below
<section className="relative z-20 -mt-14 pointer-events-none ...">
  <div className="pointer-events-auto">...</div>
</section>
```

### Canvas / animation overlays

- Particle canvases and decorative absolute layers MUST have `pointer-events-none` on every element in the stack (not only the parent).

### Navigation feedback

- Keep `NavigationProgress` in the root layout so every in-app link shows immediate feedback.
- Add or keep `loading.tsx` boundaries on slow routes (`/curriculum`, `/questions`, `/dashboard`).

### Dev server

- Bind to `127.0.0.1`, not `::`, so embedded browsers resolve `localhost` reliably.
